the name of the game is break-through.
load init-breakthrough.
ok.
if a red block is on a location that is under a clear location then you can move the block onto the clear location.
if a location is not below an object then it is clear.
if a blue block is on a location that is above a clear location then your opponent can move the block onto the clear location.
load second-breakthrough.
if an occupied location is higher than a captured location then you can move a block on the occupied location onto a garbage and you can move a block on the captured location onto the occupied location.
if a location is below a blue block then it is occupied.
if a location is under an object and the location is diagonal with the object then the object is higher than the location.
if a location is below a red block then it is captured.
if an occupied location is higher than a captured location then your opponent can move a block on the captured location onto a garbage and your opponent can move a block on the occupied location onto the captured location.
load final-breakthrough.
the goal is that a red location is captured.
you can move a block on an occupied location that is higher than a captured location onto a garbage and you can move a block on the captured location onto the occupied location.
ok.
load fail-breakthrough.
if a blue location is occupied then you lose.
ok.
done.
no.
